<TEXT>
president corazon aquino has banned 
foreign trips by administration officials except in urgent cases 
approved by her according to a presidential order published today 
mrs aquino who has visited eight countries hong kong and the 
vatican since she came to power in 1986 said the limit to foreign 
travel was necessary to conserve money and compel officials to 
perform their chores at home 
these officials should be on hand to efficiently and 
effectively manage their respective offices and be available to 
respond immediately and decisively to matters that require their 
attention she said 
manila newspapers said mrs aquino issued the order because many 
officials were traveling abroad too frequently 
during the last two years mrs aquino has traveled to 
singapore indonesia the united states japan china hong kong 
switzerland italy the vatican and brunei 
