<TEXT>
db sweeney approaches acting the way shoeless 
joe jackson played baseball just do it 
the best theory i ever heard about acting was from james 
cagney said sweeney 26 who plays jackson in john sayles 
eight men out the story of the 1919 chicago white sox scandal 
you walk in plant your feet stare the other fellow in the 
eyes and tell the truth all the acting theories ive heard all 
the books ive read you cant get it any simpler or purer than 
that 
eight men out tells the story of the biggest scandal in 
baseball the 1919 white sox were widely regarded as the best team 
of their time with such pitchers as ed cicotte and lefty williams 
and a lineup featuring future hall of famers eddie collins and ray 
schalk chicago won the american league pennant and were heavy 
favorites against the cincinnati reds in the world series 
no one however could play ball like jackson a lifetime 356 
hitter and outstanding left fielder once a mill worker in south 
carolina he had little education and could not read or write but 
was peerless on the field 
he was very passive sweeney noted he took the path of 
least resistance in everything he could everything he did was from 
a defensive mode except on the field where he attacks 
sweeney wanted to contrast jacksons athletic grace with his 
awkwardness in private life 
on the field i wanted him to be like ballet superstar 
mikhail baryshnikov i wanted every move he made to be 
beautiful sweeney said off the field i wanted him to be 
tentative 
players earned little money in jacksons era and were often 
tempted by gamblers to throw games eight members of the white sox 
including jackson agreed to or were aware of an effort to 
deliberately throw the series against cincinnati 
the reds won the series and the white sox poor play aroused 
widespread suspicion the following year commissioner kenesaw m 
landis permanently banned jackson and his seven teammates from 
baseball 
no one could ever prove that jackson who batted 375 in the 
world series ever tried to throw a game more likely he was 
punished for being aware of the fix and not trying to stop it 
they dont kick you out of the pentagon for knowing about 
fraud sweeney said adding that jackson who died in 1951 
should have his name cleared and be inducted into the baseball hall 
of fame 
daniel bernard sweeney was born and raised in shoreham ny he 
attended tulane university and hoped to play major league baseball 
until tearing ligaments in his right knee 
the injury convinced sweeney to pursue a career in acting and 
he transferred to the performing arts division of new york 
university after graduating in 1984 he appeared in the broadway 
revival of the caine mutiny 
he made his film debut in sidney lumets power and has 
since appeared in francis ford coppolas gardens of stone and 
no mans land 
although sweeney has not appeared on stage in two years he 
still prefers the working atmosphere of the theater 
on no mans land there were about four producers one 
director to start the film and one to end it we had five different 
writers and by the way we also have these actors he said 
in a play even if its a neil simon play on broadway its 
going to have to be about the actors or nobodys going to come i 
enjoy acting on stage better because there are less people with 
walkietalkies in your face 
sweeney felt an immediate rapport with sayles brother from 
another planet matewan and enjoyed working with him on the 
set 
we met in new york and talked for about an hour we talked 
about roberto clemente the late pittsburgh pirates star john 
likes the pirates hes a real bluecollar man those are the right 
reasons to like a baseball team he said 
i had access to john all the time we had a great 
relationship we would just check in with each other to gauge each 
others continued enthusiasm 
to prepare for the film sweeney traveled to kenosha wis and 
worked out with the local minor league team 
kenosha is a good town for jackson a real bluecollar town 
everybody there works for one of those corporations i think 
theres a similar ethic about work that jackson might have grown up 
with 
thats the world where jackson came from 
playing jackson boiled down to forgetting about everything 
except baseball 
i tried to stand there and clear my mind sweeney said he 
would just stand and take his three swings and more often than not 
hit it and hit it well in my daily life i have to deal with bank 
statements acting associates and friends and things its often 
like a juggling act 
 
</TEXT>
