an environmental group says it is suing the 
environmental protection agency to force the government to order a 
complete end to the use of chemicals that destroy the earths 
protective ozone layer 
the suit by the natural resources defense council challenges the 
adequacy of the partial cutbacks that epa ordered for five major 
chlorofluorocarbon compounds or cfcs on aug 1 
those regulations paralleled provisions of the 1987 treaty by 
major producing nations pledging themselves to a 50 percent 
reduction in cfc output by 1998 
the united states is the single largest contributor to 
worldwide emissions of ozonedepleting chemicals responsible 
for about 30 percent of global use david doniger an attorney for 
the council said wednesday we have a responsibility to clean up 
our own house 
</TEXT>
