<TEXT>
dr george hatem an american who served as 
doctor for mao tsetungs red army and became the first nonchinese 
citizen of the peoples republic of china has died of cancer he 
was 78 
ministry of public health official xu qiuju said today that 
hatem died monday morning family members said there would be a 
public viewing of the body on monday 
hatem who was born in 1910 to poor lebanese immigrants in 
buffalo ny is largely credited with organizing programs to 
eradicate venereal disease in china and reduce cases of leprosy by 
80 percent 
he was a senior adviser to the ministry of public health since 
1979 and sat on the governments top advisory body the chinese 
peoples political consultative conference 
dr steven b sample president of the state university of new 
york at buffalo said in a statement that over the past 
halfcentury he led the fight against dreadful diseases like 
cholera venereal disease and leprosy in china and in the process 
saved the lives of many millions of chinese 
after graduating from the university of north carolina hatem 
studied medicine at american university in beirut and received his 
medical degree from the university of geneva in 1933 he and two 
other doctors went to shanghai to study tropical medicine hatem 
lived in china for the rest of his life 
all around me were poverty malnutrition and exploitation 
hatem said in a 1983 interview i found the social evils of old 
china were more fatal to the poor than illness the problem was not 
only medical but political 
hatem said in 1984 that he first read karl marxs communist 
manifesto in shanghai its impact on me was immediate i thought 
then and think now that the poorer you are the more easily you 
understand the manifesto 
in 1936 hatem and edgar snow the journalistauthor of the 
classic red star over china answered maos call for a 
westerntrained doctor and an honest journalist they made 
their way through nationalist lines to join the communists in their 
northwestern china stronghold for the next 13 years until the 
communist triumph hatem served as medical adviser to the red army 
in 1950 hatem became the first nonchinese citizen of the new 
china he took on the chinese name of ma haide haide means 
virtue from across the seas 
in 1953 hatem helped organize the dermatology and venereology 
research institute and by the end of the decade china claimed that 
oncepandemic syphilis and gonorrhea had been eliminated venereal 
disease has again become a minor problem in recent years as chinas 
opendoor policy increases contacts with the outside world 
in the 1960s hatem turned to a new program to control leprosy 
with a goal of eradicating the disease which still afflicts about 
70000 chinese by the year 2000 
his death had not yet been reported in the tightly controlled 
official chinese press possibly because it occurred during chinese 
national day holidays 
hatem is survived by his wife of 50 years chou sufei a son a 
daughter a sister and four grandchildren 
