geoffrey household whose adventure novels include 
the tale of an english hunter who stalks adolf hitler is dead at 
age 87 his family said thursday 
the writers home was near banbury 65 miles from london the 
family said he died tuesday and no cause of death was given 
household said the story of an attempt to kill hitler came to 
him because the man had to be dealt with and i began to think how 
much i would love to kill him 
the hero of rogue male published in 1939 is an 
aristocratic biggame hunter who is caught and tortured by the 
nazis but escapes 
during world war ii household served as a commando in romania 
and later as an intelligence officer in greece palestine syria 
and iraq 
he was educated at oxford then traveled and worked at various 
jobs in europe the near east south america and the united states 
he used the impressions gained from his travels in his novels 
a magazine financed him to write the the third hour a novel 
published in 1937 his first book of short stories the salvation 
of pisco gabar appeared in 1938 
household resumed writing after the war producing adventure 
stories with such titles as a rough shoot in 1951 and watcher 
in the shadows in 1960 
he also wrote picaresque romances childrens books stories 
about the supernatural and an autobiography against the wind 
published in 1958 
surviving are his wife ilona zsoldosgutman a son and two 
daughters 
