the government was defrauded of more than 1 billion in connection 
with the manufacture of the mx missileguidance system 
the suit brought by eight current and former northrop employees 
accuses the companys electronics division of intentionally 
delivering to the air force defective inertial measurement units 
which guide the mx peacekeeper missile 
the 67page complaint unsealed wednesday in us district court 
in los angeles and filed in october 1987 says northrop failed to 
ensure that the guidance components were properly manufactured 
controlled processed and inspected it says northrop wrongfully 
received 1 billion from the government and seeks three times that 
