also must realize the kind of turmoil she set in place as a result 
of her false allegations 
i think she needs help and should get as much help as possible 
so her life can be salvaged 
miss brawleys mother glenda faces a 30day jail term for 
contempt after refusing to answer a grand jury subpoena at the 
advisers urging but has so far escaped arrest at one point 
seeking sanctuary in a church 
her daughter also defied a subpoena but was not cited for 
contempt miss brawley left her new home in virginia beach va 
thursday without comment 
thursday night sharpton led about 200 people in a demonstration 
outside the offices of the new york times which reported details 
of the grand jurys report last week sharpton said events showed 
the newspaper had illegal access to the grand jurys findings 
sharpton said he and miss brawley would be in chicago on 
saturday to give our complete and official reaction 
the grand jury heard more than 180 witnesses the probe cost 
taxpayers at least 620000 and the case was investigated 
perhaps in a more thorough way than any other case in the history 
of the state abrams said 
the report examined miss brawleys behavior down to a 
microscopic level including analyses of dog hairs found in feces 
burn marks on miss brawleys jeans and carpet fibers found in her 
former apartment 
the report concluded miss brawley spent much of her time during 
the four days at the apartment 
the report said miss brawley apparently burned a hole in her 
pants scrawled nigger on her shoe smeared dog feces on her 
body and clothing and stepped into a plastic garbage bag in front 
of the apartment 
the grand jury issued recommendations to the legislature for 
legal reforms including a proposal that would allow the relative 
of a dead person to bring a defamation case when the individual is 
falsely accused of a felony 
abrams and the grand jury also recommended enactment of an 
obstruction of justice law 
new york has a law against obstruction of governmental 
administration but it cannot be used against maddox and mason 
because it applies only when a threat of violence or a separate 
criminal act is employed the attorney general said 
he also called for changes in a state law that prevented him 
from moving against those who helped protect mrs brawley from 
arrest for contempt 
under state law people can be charged with harboring a fugitive 
only if the offense for which the fugitive is wanted is a felony 
abrams said the contempt charge was not a felony 
