the communist party bosses of 
yugoslavs vojvodina province were ousted thursday night as a 
stonethrowing crowd of 30000 people attacked their headquarters 
the provincial leaders had promised to resign after a meeting 
with serbian leaders earlier thursday in the most dramatic 
development in three months of mass street protests over ethnic 
strife and an economic crisis 
the development boosted a drive by serbia yugoslavias largest 
republic for tighter control over its two autonomous provinces 
vojvodina and ethnically troubled kosovo 
at least 41 people including 14 policemen were injured when 
the crowd outside the headquarters in this provincial capital of 
novi sad surged toward riot police guarding the building hurling 
stones and breaking 20 windows 
staterun news media said two policemen were seriously hurt and 
six people were hospitalized four people were reported arrested 
the protesters who held vigil outside the headquarters for two 
days began to disperse after the leadership stepped down 
witnesses said police rebuffed an attempt by the crowds 
