<TEXT>
here are some of the key events in the bank of new york cos 
hostile takeover bid for control of irving bank corp 
sept 25 1987 bank of new york makes an unsolicited 14 
billion cashstock bid for irving 
oct 9 irvings board rejects the bid activating the 
companys poison pill antitakeover defense 
nov 20 bank of new york lowers its offer to 12 billion 
citing the oct 19 stock market crash 
dec 15 irvings board rejects the new bid 
jan 25 1988 bank of new york lowers its bid to 108 
billion citing irvings decision to increase its fourthquarter 
loanloss reserve 
feb 16 irvings board rejects the 108 billion bid 
feb 25 bank of new yorks takeover proposal gets approval 
from the federal reserve and new york state banking boards 
march 15 28 irving strengthens its poison pill 
april 14 bank of new yorks shareholders give their blessing 
to a merger with irving 
april 18 banca commerciale italiana enters the picture 
offering to buy 51 percent of irving as part of a major financial 
resturcturing announced by irving that it values at about 11 
billion12 billion the two revise the proposed deal several 
times in the following weeks raising the estimated value to 14 
billion 
may 6 irvings shareholders reelect irvings directors 
although bank of new york later challenges the proxy results in 
court 
june 15 bank of new york conditionally offers to raise the 
stock portion of its bid valuing the offer at 14 billion irving 
later rejects the proposal the previous offer valued at about 
12 billion under current market conditions stands 
july 6 a new york state court strikes down a provision of 
irvings poison pill irving vows to appeal 
aug 19 the fed rules the italian government agency that owns 
most of banca commerciale has to supply financial information in 
the irving bid 
aug 29 banca commerciale withdraws its bid 
sept 7 the fed grants bank of new york another 90day 
extension to complete the irving merger 
oct 4 the new york state supreme courts appellate division 
upholds the lower court ruling that struck down a part of irvings 
poison pill 
oct 5 irving announces its chairman now supports a revised 
15 billion merger proposal by the bank of new york 
